Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The death toll in the Rift Valley fever outbreak along the Nile
valley in central Sudan is now 84, having increased by 24 since the
previous WHO report. The case number has risen more dramatically from
125 to 228, possibly indicated enhanced surveillance. There is still
no indication of the extent of animal disease associated with this
outbreak. Information from an informed source would be welcomed.

A map of Sudan showing the location of the adjacent states of White
Nile, Sinnar, and Gezira, just south of the capital Khartoum is available at
<http://www.rightsmaps.com/html/sudmap1.html>. - Mod.CP

The HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of Sudan can be accessed at
<http://healthmap.org/promed?v=13.8,30,5>. - CopyEd.MJ]
